WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:07.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: After days of
setbacks, a Cabinet
nominee dropping out, a resigned
national

00:07.608 --> 00:12.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
security adviser, and a court
rejection of
his travel ban, President Trump
went on the

00:12.813 --> 00:14.715 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
offensive today.

00:14.748 --> 00:21.555 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At a 77-minute-long news
conference, he rejected
charges of ties between his
campaign and Russia,

00:21.588 --> 00:26.193 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
blasted the intelligence
community for leaks,
and repeatedly attacked the news
media.

00:26.226 --> 00:31.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president said he inherited
a mess at
home and abroad, but he
dismissed the notion

00:31.531 --> 00:33.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of a White House in turmoil.

00:33.333 --> 00:36.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
I turn on the TV, open the
newspapers and

00:36.270 --> 00:38.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I see stories of chaos.

00:38.939 --> 00:40.307 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Chaos.

00:40.340 --> 00:42.175 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Yet it is the exact opposite.

00:42.209 --> 00:52.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This administration is running
like a fine-tuned
machine, despite the fact that I
can't get

00:52.185 --> 00:54.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
my Cabinet approved.

00:54.488 --> 00:58.825 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Let me list to you some of the
things that
we've done in just a short
period of time.

00:58.859 --> 01:00.394 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I just got here.

01:00.427 --> 01:03.163 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I got here with no Cabinet.

01:03.196 --> 01:08.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Again, each of these actions is
a promise
I made to the American people.

01:08.302 --> 01:09.836 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, I will go over just some of
them.

01:09.870 --> 01:15.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we have a lot happening next
week and
in the weeks --in the weeks
coming.

01:15.342 --> 01:20.681 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We've withdrawn from the
job-killing disaster
known as Trans-Pacific
Partnership.

01:20.714 --> 01:25.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're going to make trade deals,
but we're
going to have one-on-one deals,
bilateral.

01:25.986 --> 01:30.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We've undertaken the most
substantial border
security measures in a
generation to keep

01:30.857 --> 01:36.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our nation and our tax dollars
safe, and are
now in the process of beginning
to build a

01:36.163 --> 01:38.465 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
promised wall on the southern
border.

01:38.498 --> 01:43.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The price is going to come down
just like
it has on everything else I have
negotiated

01:43.270 --> 01:44.271 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the government.

01:44.304 --> 01:46.840 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we are going to have a wall
that works.

01:46.873 --> 01:51.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're not going to have a wall
like they have
now, which is either nonexistent
or a joke.

01:51.645 --> 01:56.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We've begun preparing to repeal
and replace
Obamacare.

01:56.216 --> 01:58.785 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Obamacare is a disaster, folks.

01:58.819 --> 01:59.786 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's disaster.

01:59.820 --> 02:02.456 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I know you can say, oh,
Obamacare.

02:02.489 --> 02:09.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, they fill up our alleys
with people
that you wonder how they get
there, but they

02:09.997 --> 02:14.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are not the Republican people
our that representatives
are representing.

02:14.634 --> 02:21.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we've begun preparing to
repeal and replace
Obamacare, and are deep in the
midst of negotiations

02:21.875 --> 02:28.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on a very historic tax reform to
bring our
jobs back, to bring our jobs
back to this

02:28.382 --> 02:29.349 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
country, big league.

02:29.383 --> 02:31.952 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's already happening, but big
league.

02:31.985 --> 02:37.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have kept my promise to the
American people
by nominating a justice of the
United States

02:37.624 --> 02:44.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Supreme Court, Judge Neil
Gorsuch, who is
from my list of 20, and who will
be a true

02:44.765 --> 02:51.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
defender of our laws and our
Constitution,
highly respected, should get the
votes from

02:51.271 --> 02:52.239 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Democrats.

02:52.272 --> 02:53.640 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You may not see that.

02:53.673 --> 02:56.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But he'll get there one way or
the other.

02:56.343 --> 03:02.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This last month has represented
an unprecedented
degree of action on behalf of
the great citizens

03:02.783 --> 03:03.750 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of our country.

03:03.784 --> 03:05.485 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Again, I say it.

03:05.519 --> 03:12.959 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There has never been a
presidency that's done
so much in such a short period
of time.

03:12.993 --> 03:15.262 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we have not even started the
big work
yet.

03:15.295 --> 03:16.963 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That starts early next week.

03:16.997 --> 03:21.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The president
also faced
repeated questions about Russian
contacts

03:21.168 --> 03:27.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with officials in his campaign
and about firing
National Security Adviser Mike
Flynn.

03:27.107 --> 03:32.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Washington Post reported
this evening
Flynn denied to the FBI last
month that he

03:32.379 --> 03:38.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
discussed lifting sanctions with
the Russian
ambassador, but intercepted
communications

03:38.151 --> 03:39.653 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
indicate he did.

03:39.686 --> 03:45.725 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Mike Flynn is a
fine person,
and I asked for his resignation.

03:45.759 --> 03:47.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He respectfully gave it.

03:47.994 --> 03:54.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is a man who there was a
certain amount
of information given to Vice
President Pence,

03:54.234 --> 03:56.803 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
who is with us today.

03:56.837 --> 04:01.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I was not happy with the way
that information
was given.

04:01.441 --> 04:08.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He didn't have to do that,
because what he
did wasn't wrong -- what he did
in terms of

04:08.582 --> 04:11.418 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the information he saw.

04:11.451 --> 04:16.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What was wrong was the way that
other people,
including yourselves in this
room, were given

04:16.857 --> 04:21.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that information, because that
was classified
information that was given
illegally.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.062 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's the real problem.

04:22.095 --> 04:24.931 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
QUESTION: What will you do on
the leaks?

04:24.965 --> 04:26.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You've said twice today...

04:26.366 --> 04:28.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Yes, we're looking
at them very
-- very, very serious.

04:28.135 --> 04:33.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have gone to all of the folks
in charge
of the various agencies, and
we're -- I have

04:33.707 --> 04:38.011 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
actually called the Justice
Department to
look into the leaks.

04:38.044 --> 04:39.713 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Those are criminal leaks.

04:39.746 --> 04:44.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're put out by people either
in agencies
-- I think you'll see it
stopping because

04:44.918 --> 04:46.653 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
now we have our people in.

04:46.686 --> 04:49.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, again, we don't have
our people
in because we can't get them
approved by the

04:49.823 --> 04:51.591 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Senate.

04:51.625 --> 04:54.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: Did you direct Mike
Flynn to discuss
sanctions with the Russian
ambassador...

04:54.327 --> 04:55.562 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: No, I didn't.

04:55.595 --> 04:56.563 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
QUESTION: ... prior to your...

04:56.596 --> 04:57.631 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: No, I didn't.

04:57.664 --> 04:58.632 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
QUESTION: ... inauguration?

04:58.665 --> 04:59.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: No, I didn't.

04:59.666 --> 05:00.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
QUESTION: And then fired him...

05:00.734 --> 05:01.701 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP: Excuse me.

05:01.735 --> 05:03.136 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

05:03.170 --> 05:03.703 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: No, I fired him
because of what
he said to Mike Pence.

05:03.737 --> 05:04.704 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Very simple.

05:04.738 --> 05:05.805 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Mike was doing his job.

05:05.839 --> 05:08.275 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He was calling countries and his
counterparts.

05:08.308 --> 05:11.444 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it certainly would have been
OK with me
if he did it.

05:11.478 --> 05:14.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would have directed him to do
it if I thought
he wasn't doing it.

05:15.015 --> 05:18.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I didn't direct him, but I would
have directed
him because that's his job.

05:18.952 --> 05:23.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: During the campaign,
did anyone
from your team communicate with
members of

05:23.390 --> 05:24.491 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Russian government or
Russian intelligence?

05:24.524 --> 05:27.460 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, if so, what was the nature
of those conversations?

05:27.494 --> 05:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: And I can tell
you, speaking
for myself, I own nothing in
Russia.

05:33.066 --> 05:36.036 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have no loans in Russia.

05:36.069 --> 05:40.073 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't have any deals in
Russia.

05:40.106 --> 05:45.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Putin called me up
very nicely to
congratulate me on the win of
the election.

05:45.312 --> 05:51.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He then called me up extremely
nicely to congratulate
me on the inauguration, which
was terrific.

05:51.918 --> 05:56.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But so did many other leaders,
almost all
other leaders from almost all of
the countries.

05:56.623 --> 05:58.725 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So that's the extent.

05:58.758 --> 06:00.193 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Russia is fake news.

06:00.227 --> 06:03.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russia -- this is fake news put
out by the
media.

06:03.363 --> 06:09.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The false reporting by the
media, by you people,
the false, horrible, fake
reporting makes

06:09.803 --> 06:13.740 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it much harder to make a deal
with Russia.

06:13.773 --> 06:19.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And probably Putin said, you
know -- he's
sitting behind his desk, and
he's saying,

06:19.179 --> 06:22.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you know, I see what's going on
in the United
States.

06:22.048 --> 06:23.783 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I follow it closely.

06:23.817 --> 06:28.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's going to be impossible for
President
Trump to ever get along with
Russia because

06:28.722 --> 06:31.992 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of all the pressure he's got
with this fake
story, OK?

06:32.025 --> 06:33.927 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
QUESTION: Is Putin testing you,
do you believe,
sir?

06:33.960 --> 06:35.862 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: No, I don't think
so.

06:35.895 --> 06:40.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think Putin probably assumes
that he can't
make a deal with me anymore
because politically

06:40.100 --> 06:42.869 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it would be unpopular for a
politician to
make a deal.

06:42.902 --> 06:45.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I can't believe I'm saying I'm a
politician,
but I guess that's what I am
now.

06:45.805 --> 06:49.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Because, look, it would be much
easier for
me to be tough on Russia, but
then we're not

06:49.476 --> 06:50.577 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
going to make a deal.

06:50.610 --> 06:52.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, I don't know that we're
going to make
a deal.

06:52.078 --> 06:53.179 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I don't know.

06:53.213 --> 06:54.180 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We might.

06:54.214 --> 06:56.082 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We might not.

06:56.116 --> 06:59.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it would be much easier for
me to be so
tough -- the tougher I am on
Russia, the better.

06:59.419 --> 07:00.520 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But you know what?

07:00.553 --> 07:04.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to do the right thing for
the American
people.

07:04.357 --> 07:07.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And to be honest, secondarily, I
want to do
the right thing for the world.

07:07.927 --> 07:12.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: I was just hoping that
we could
get a yes-or-no answer on one of
these questions

07:12.399 --> 07:14.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
involving Russia.

07:14.301 --> 07:18.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Can you say whether you are
aware that anyone
who advised your campaign had
contacts with

07:18.071 --> 07:19.773 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Russia during the course of the
election?

07:19.806 --> 07:22.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Well, I told you,
General Flynn
obviously was dealing.

07:22.976 --> 07:23.943 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So that's one person.

07:23.977 --> 07:25.478 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But he was dealing, as he should
have been.

07:25.512 --> 07:26.680 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
QUESTION: During the election?

07:26.713 --> 07:27.681 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP: No.

07:27.714 --> 07:28.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Nobody that I know of.

07:28.715 --> 07:30.050 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Nobody...

07:30.083 --> 07:30.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
QUESTION: So you're not aware of
any contact
during the course...

07:30.884 --> 07:31.651 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Look, look,
look...

07:31.685 --> 07:33.019 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
QUESTION: ... of the election?

07:33.053 --> 07:33.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: How many times do
I have to
answer this question?

07:33.920 --> 07:34.654 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
QUESTION: Can you just say yes
or no?

07:34.688 --> 07:35.655 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: Russia is a ruse.

07:35.689 --> 07:36.690 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I know you have to get up and
ask a question.

07:36.723 --> 07:37.691 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's so important.

07:37.724 --> 07:39.359 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But Russia is a ruse.

07:39.392 --> 07:41.528 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have nothing to do with
Russia.

07:41.561 --> 07:44.397 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Haven't made a phone call to
Russia in years.

07:44.431 --> 07:45.832 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Don't speak to people from
Russia.

07:45.865 --> 07:46.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Not that I wouldn't.

07:46.866 --> 07:48.568 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I just have nobody to speak to.

07:48.601 --> 07:50.270 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I spoke to Putin twice.

07:50.303 --> 07:51.871 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He called me on the election.

07:51.905 --> 07:53.273 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I told you this.

07:53.306 --> 07:56.076 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And he called me on the
inauguration, a few
days ago.

07:56.109 --> 08:03.483 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We had a very good talk,
especially the second
one, lasted for a pretty long
period of time.

08:03.516 --> 08:06.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm sure you probably get it
because it was
classified.

08:06.086 --> 08:08.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I'm sure everybody in this
room perhaps
has it.

08:09.022 --> 08:11.124 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But we had a very, very good
talk.

08:11.157 --> 08:13.059 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have nothing to do with
Russia.

08:13.093 --> 08:16.730 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To the best of my knowledge, no
person that
I deal with does.

08:16.763 --> 08:22.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mr. Trump also
defended his
ban on travelers from seven
mostly Muslim

08:22.736 --> 08:23.703 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
nations.

08:23.737 --> 08:25.405 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's been blocked in federal
court.

08:25.438 --> 08:29.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, the Justice Department
announced that
the order will be rescinded.

08:29.642 --> 08:33.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president said that a new
one is coming,
and he addressed the fate of
immigrant children

08:33.913 --> 08:37.117 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
shielded from deportation under
the so-called
DACA program.

08:37.150 --> 08:40.920 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
