to do that
yet.

19:45.418 --> 19:49.455 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's why it hasn't been
released yet, the
White House still designing this
executive

19:49.488 --> 19:50.589 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
order.

19:50.623 --> 19:52.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But pay attention to Mr. Trump's
words today,
Hari.

19:52.591 --> 19:57.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He also said that this is
extreme vetting,
that they had to move up more
quickly because

19:57.830 --> 19:59.598 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the Ninth Circuit ruling.

19:59.632 --> 20:03.636 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So this is something they were
looking at
more long-term that they seem to
be incorporating

20:03.669 --> 20:05.471 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
into an executive order next
week.

20:05.504 --> 20:09.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It doesn't seem like it's all
the way fully
baked, but it's going to be
significant when

20:09.275 --> 20:10.509 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
it comes.

20:10.543 --> 20:12.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Lisa, finally,
why did they
have this today?

20:12.545 --> 20:14.246 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Why did they have this press
conference, briefly?

20:14.280 --> 20:16.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I think there
were a lot
of reasons, obviously, just the
headlines

20:16.649 --> 20:19.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
themselves and the White House
struggling
to respond to them.

20:19.385 --> 20:21.454 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They wanted to get the president
out himself
