transition.

20:50.449 --> 20:52.651 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Washington Post columnist
Ruth Marcus.

20:52.685 --> 20:55.321 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Welcome back to the program to
both of you.

20:55.354 --> 20:57.323 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ruth, I'm going to start with
you.

20:57.356 --> 21:02.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the first sort of
wide-ranging, full-blown
news conference we have seen
from this president

21:02.294 --> 21:03.796 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in several weeks.

21:03.829 --> 21:05.764 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What did you make of it overall?

21:05.798 --> 21:09.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS, Columnist, The
Washington Post:
It was, as everybody has been
saying, an extraordinary

21:09.802 --> 21:10.769 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
event.

21:10.803 --> 21:14.240 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think it had kind of three
audiences.

21:14.273 --> 21:17.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One audience was the president
himself.

21:17.343 --> 21:21.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think he likes to do this sort
of government
by improv.

21:21.147 --> 21:22.515 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He did campaign by improv.

21:22.548 --> 21:23.582 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
